member.summary:
Remove regions from a query based on include parameter given the following query syntax:
 {regionName}? {
    query region to exclude/include
 }

Searches given text in the specified fields. This method must be used in case there is a requirement to perform a search in nested sub fields and the field names of the sub fields are unknown.
Example: Query.multiMatch(Arrays.asList("content.*", "otherfields*"), "searchvalue");
The query operator is OR. Important note: the operator in multi match queries works on the given terms and not on the fields.

Searches given text in the specified fields. This method must be used in case there is a requirement to perform a search in nested sub fields and the field names of the sub fields are unknown.
Example: Query.multiMatch(Arrays.asList("content.*", "otherfields*"), "searchvalue");
The given query operator is used. Important note: the operator in multi match queries works on the given terms and not on the fields.

Grouped AND query on multiple fields and values.
Example: GroupedAnd({"id","type"},{"1","page"}
becomes: +(+id:1 +type:page) List lengths must match or query param may be smaller.
